<br>
But then something happened - I got a burnt book (couple months back) and just this weekend a frost book (off of Gorenaire)! I had already completed Soulfire and GB Quests for fun (had sold my old camped for GB loooong ago) and honestly at your level they are really easy. <br>
<br>
Now that I have the books - the rest of the quest really isn't that hard. It's true by the time I complete it I may have better... but right now I don't (Argent Protector) so I might as well go for it.<br>
<br>
I think that's the attitude you should have, if/when you end up with the books go ahead and complete the quest - if not, no worries, there is lots out there nearly as good and plenty that is better. In the meantime GB and soulfire quests are fun and shouldn't take up that much time. You can also use your soulfire for Cheals on raids...<br>
<br>
Kinda sucks that our &quot;Epic&quot; isn't really so epic, but who knows with the rumors of truly epic epics in the future, I'm sure that the FD will be part of that quest (like FA was for FD...). <br>
<br>
My 2cp  <p>Knight of Tarew Marr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unesued.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nesued</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/25/02 3:00:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15032.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EPIC is it worth it?</span><hr size=1> Being a High- Elven-Tunare-worshipping Paladin, I had an option most of my fellow Paladin brothers don't:  <br>
<br>
Nature's Defender.<br>
<br>
I decided to settle for that as my "Epic", and forget all of this "epic-angst".  I have too many of my brethren in the "level 52 and holding" mentality.  <br>
<br>
Personally, I see that as contributing to the lack of higher level Paladins making an impact on raids, ect.  Perhaps it's not because of what we can't do, but because there are fewer of us to actually MAKE a difference.  Combine the fact of the "Hybrid" nature, with this imposed "holding pattern" makes for less chances of us to participate in the "high-end" game environment.<br>
