<br>
To me the epic is worth it.  Then again I run around in full deepwater when I could/can get access to tov drops.  I don't roleplay, but the sense of how my character is decided that the epic is the only weapon for me.  I've had access to better 1hdrs then epic also, but passed on them.  <br>
<br>
It just boils down to how you want to play and how much it really means to you. <p>Chavr Wyrmbane<br>
58 Knight of Mithaniel Marr<br>
Coven Nex<br>
Druzzil Ro<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urilkar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rilkar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/25/02 3:17:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15032.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.users.qwest.net/~user35521/Rilkar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EPIC is it worth it?</span><hr size=1> Some classes like their epic because they really get a unique or significantly enhanced ability off their epics.  Clerics are a classic example.  With their eipc, just a couple of clerics can rez a whole raid without using any manna or needing to med.  Another example is Mages.  Their epic brings them an enhanced ability that they would not have otherwise.<br>
<br>
Our epic is just a weapon that procs a DD.  There are other weapons out there with similar or even better damage/delay ratios.  Some of them even proc a DD.<br>
<br>
I have everything I need for my epic except the dragon books.  At 46-52 my RL schedule prevented me from going on dragon raids, and the guild i am currently in just doesn't do Kunark dragons that much.<br>
<br>
I currently have a weapon with a better damage/delay ratio that even procs a stronger DD.  So I doubt I'll ever get my epic, but I don't think I'm missing much.  A lot of the Paladins in my guild that have epics have put them in the bank in favor of other weapons.<br>
<br>
There's talk and rumors of epic upgrades, but until I see them, I'm not going to lose too much sleep over it.<br>
<br>
If you want your epic because you would feel pride and satisfaction in getting it, and that would be a fun use of your leisure time, then go for it.  But from a purely game mechanics point of view, I don't think it's worth the trouble unless you already have the dragon books.<br>
<br>
